prevent all forms of violence against children in all settings, including 
corporal punishment, and to strengthen the awareness-raising activities 
(Slovenia); 
</b></p>
<p><b>38. Take all measures to address and prevent abduction of children, child 
trafficking, sexual abuse and exploitation and child labour, including the 
prosecution of perpetrators of such acts, and to protect and reintegrate 
child victims (Slovenia); 
</b></p>
<p><b>39. Take all measures to ensure the protection of children from trafficking 
and bring perpetrators of child trafficking to justice (Angola); 
</b></p>
<p><b>40. Put in place, with the support of UNICEF, permanent structures against 
the exploitation of children as cattle herders (Democratic Republic of the 
